

The platform is based on collaboration, where there are existing startup opportunities, freelance projects that are handled with colancing or teamlancing, events, and circles.

In the circles section (simply put, chatrooms for various purposes), we have three types of circles, opportunity circles, community circles, and event circles. Opportunity circles are private cricles that the system generates whenever an opportunity (startup roles or project posting) is posted, anyone who applied to this particular opportunity, and got accepted, shall be added to this room, where the team shall proceed with their respective tasks. the community circles are the public cricles, where interaction, PR and engagement on the platform occurs, these circles are the ones capable of creating events. two or more community circles can collaborate to create an event, one circle simply has to send a collab request to another circle with a proposal, and the request when accepted, creates an event. Event circles are temporary circles that have a fixed tenure, and are attached to a particular event with which they are created automatically. these contain all the members from both the community circles.

In the events section, the user sees various events in which he or she may take part in. various events created by different circles shall be displayed here.

In the startups section, one can post various roles available for his/her startup, along with available startup opportunities. when u post an opportunity, an opportunity circle is created, u accepted an reject the application on the opportunity, and those accepted, rejected etc are notified, accepted ones are added directly to the opp. circle.

